>Description<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/Signal#description\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n  <p>Signals are functions which returns their current value. To access the current value of a signal,\ncall it.</p>\n<p>Ordinary values can be turned into <code><a href=\"api/core/Signal\" class=\"code-anchor\">Signal</a></code>s with the <code><a href=\"api/core/signal\" class=\"code-anchor\">signal</a></code> function.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - api/core\n - api/core/ContentChildFunction\n - api/core/InputSignal\n - api/core/InputSignalWithTransform\n - api/core/ModelSignal\n - api/core/ViewChildFunction\n - api/core/WritableSignal\n - api/core/computed\n - api/core/contentChild\n - api/core/contentChildren\n - api/core/input\n - api/core/isSignal\n - api/core/rxjs-interop\n - api/core/rxjs-interop/toObservable\n - api/core/rxjs-interop/toSignal\n - api/core/signal\n - api/core/viewChild\n - api/core/viewChildren\n - extended-diagnostics/NG8109\n - guide/rxjs-interop\n - guide/signal-inputs\n - guide/signal-queries\n - guide/signals\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - /api\n - api/core\n - api/core/Signal#description\n - api/core/Signal#signal\n - api/core/signal\n - https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/17.3.12/packages/core/src/render3/reactivity/api.ts#L10-L21\n-->"
